// (#331 L2b) A LAUNDERED aliased free: `xs` is captured into the container `ys` by a call
// (`ys = push(ys, xs)`), so `ys[0]` still holds `xs`'s buffer — freeing `xs` dangles it. The spine's
// capture sweep marks a non-scalar bare local passed as a non-`free` call argument `us = shared`, so
// the affine `mem::free` guard REJECTS it. Closes the container-store launder class (option b).
// Compile-reject on both engines (EXPECT_COMPILE_FAIL).
use cc

(cc::run()) to i32
